<doc id="638107" wikidata="Q7116334" url="?curid=638107" title="Oyster plant">
<text>Oyster plant is a common name used for various flowering plants, including:

*&quot;Acanthus mollis&quot;, (also called bear&#x27;s breeches), native to the Mediterranean
*&quot;Mertensia maritima&quot; (also called oysterleaf), native to Europe and North America with leaves said to taste like oysters
*&quot;Pseudopodospermum hispanicum&quot; (also called black salsify), cultivated for its dark-skinned edible root
*&quot;Tragopogon porrifolius&quot; (also called purple salsify), cultivated for its light-skinned edible root
*&quot;Tradescantia spathacea&quot; (synonyms &quot;Tradescantia discolor&quot;, &quot;Rhoeo spathacea&quot;, &quot;Rhoeo discolor&quot;); (also called Oyster Herb, Daun Kepah, Nanas Kerang, Boatlily (Cây Lẻ Bạn, Lảo Bạn, Sò Huyết), Moses in a basket, Cradle Lily, Moses in His Cradle, Moses on a Raft, Moses in the Bulrushes, Men in a Boat, Moses-in-Cradle, (Chinese) 蚌花) </text><links>
